# Horion.pro Design System v1.0

This rule applies to every file under `apps/web/`. All new components and edits **must** follow these specifications exactly. No deviations.

---

## Brand

- Platform name: **Horion** / **horion.pro**
- **Tagline / positioning:** **Reliability Engineering Platform** — use under the logo (nav, landing, auth), in `layout.tsx` metadata, and anywhere a one-line product descriptor is needed.
- **Scope:** Horion is a reliability engineering product. Today, analyses focus on **observability** (metrics, logs, traces instrumentation); additional domains will follow. Do **not** use the deprecated tagline **"Observability Platform"** for the product as a whole.
- Never write "Lumis" in UI copy, metadata, or localStorage keys.
- localStorage / sessionStorage key prefix: `hz-` (e.g. `hz-theme`, `hz-token`, `hz-api-key`, `hz-pending-invite`)

---

## Font

**JetBrains Mono** exclusively — for all text: headings, body, labels, buttons, inputs, nav, numbers, code.

```tsx
// Already imported in layout.tsx via next/font/google — no additional import needed.
// Never use system fonts, Inter, or any other sans-serif.
```

---

## Color — CSS Variables Only

All colors come from `--hz-*` CSS variables defined in `globals.css`. **Never** use Tailwind color classes (`text-gray-*`, `bg-blue-*`, `border-red-*`, etc.) in components.

Tailwind is for **layout and spacing only**: `flex`, `grid`, `gap`, `p`, `m`, `w`, `h`, `overflow`, `items-*`, `justify-*`, `rounded-*` (layout), `space-*`, `col-span-*`, `shrink-0`, etc.

### Light mode tokens (`:root`)

| Token | Value | Role |
|-------|-------|------|
| `--hz-bg` | `#ffffff` | Page background |
| `--hz-bg2` | `#f8f8f6` | Sidebar, filter bars |
| `--hz-bg3` | `#f0f0ec` | Hover, active nav, surface |
| `--hz-bg4` | `#e8e8e2` | Avatars, deep surface |
| `--hz-ink` | `#0a0a0a` | Primary text, logo |
| `--hz-ink2` | `#3a3a3a` | Body text, secondary labels |
| `--hz-muted` | `#888880` | Muted text, placeholders, nav inactive |
| `--hz-rule` | `#e4e4de` | Dividers, borders |
| `--hz-rule2` | `#d0d0c8` | Stronger borders, input borders |

### Semantic tokens (both modes — analysis / reliability signals (findings, grades, status, etc.), never decorative)

| Token | Light | Dark | Use |
|-------|-------|------|-----|
| `--hz-crit` | `#c0392b` | `#f87171` | Critical findings |
| `--hz-crit-bg` | `#fef2f2` | `#2d1515` | Critical badge background |
| `--hz-crit-bd` | `#fca5a5` | `#7f1d1d` | Critical badge border |
| `--hz-warn` | `#b7791f` | `#fbbf24` | Warning findings |
| `--hz-warn-bg` | `#fffbeb` | `#261d08` | Warning badge background |
| `--hz-warn-bd` | `#fcd34d` | `#78350f` | Warning badge border |
| `--hz-ok` | `#276749` | `#4ade80` | Completed, grade A |
| `--hz-ok-bg` | `#ecfdf5` | `#0d2416` | OK badge background |
| `--hz-ok-bd` | `#6ee7b7` | `#14532d` | OK badge border |
| `--hz-info` | `#1a4480` | `#60a5fa` | Running, grade B |
| `--hz-info-bg` | `#eff6ff` | `#0d1e3a` | Info badge background |

### Usage in JSX

```tsx
// CORRECT — CSS vars via style prop
<div style={{ background: 'var(--hz-bg2)', borderBottom: '1px solid var(--hz-rule)' }}>

// CORRECT — Tailwind layout + CSS var inline style
<div className="flex items-center gap-3 px-4" style={{ color: 'var(--hz-ink)' }}>

// WRONG — Tailwind color classes
<div className="bg-gray-100 text-gray-900 border-gray-200">  {/* ✗ never */}
```

---

## Spacing

`4 8 12 16 24 32 48 64px` — use Tailwind spacing utilities (`p-2`, `gap-4`, etc.) for these values.

## Radius

| Token | Value |
|-------|-------|
| `--hz-sm` | `4px` |
| `--hz-md` | `8px` |
| `--hz-lg` | `12px` |

Use `border-radius: var(--hz-md)` in style props, or Tailwind `rounded-md` / `rounded-lg` for structural elements.

## Borders & Shadows

- Borders: always `1px solid var(--hz-rule)` or `var(--hz-rule2)` — never thicker for decoration.
- Shadows: **none** — zero `box-shadow`. Use borders instead.

---

## Typography Scale

All text is JetBrains Mono. Use the `.hz-*` global CSS classes or inline styles:

| Scale | Size | Weight | Tracking | Class |
|-------|------|--------|----------|-------|
| hero | 40px | 700 | -0.03em | `.hz-hero` |
| h1 | 28px | 700 | -0.025em | `.hz-h1` |
| h2 | 20px | 500 | — | `.hz-h2` |
| body | 14px | 400 | — | `.hz-body` (color: ink2, line-height 1.7) |
| mono-sm | 12px | 400 | — | `.hz-sm` (color: muted) |
| label | 10px | 400 | 0.16em | `.hz-label` (uppercase, muted) |
| micro | 10px | 400 | — | `.hz-micro` |

