## Component Specs

### Button

```tsx
// Use global CSS classes:
<button className="hz-btn hz-btn-primary">start free</button>
<button className="hz-btn hz-btn-outline">see pricing</button>
<button className="hz-btn hz-btn-ghost">log in</button>

// Specs: padding 9px 18px / border-radius 8px / font-size 13px / letter-spacing -0.01em
// Primary: bg var(--hz-ink) / color var(--hz-bg)
// Outline: bg transparent / border var(--hz-ink) / color var(--hz-ink)
// Ghost: bg transparent / border var(--hz-rule2) / color var(--hz-ink2)
```

### Badge (semantic only — no decorative colors)

```tsx
<div className="hz-badge hz-badge-crit"><span className="hz-dot" />3 critical</div>
<div className="hz-badge hz-badge-warn"><span className="hz-dot" />11 warning</div>
<div className="hz-badge hz-badge-ok"><span className="hz-dot" />completed</div>
<div className="hz-badge hz-badge-info"><span className="hz-dot" />running</div>
// Running dot pulses — animation built into hz-badge-info .hz-dot in globals.css
```

### Score Gauge

```tsx
<div className="hz-score">
  <div className="hz-score-num" style={{ color: 'var(--hz-ok)' }}>77</div>
  <div className="hz-score-grade hz-grade-b">B</div>
  <div className="hz-score-lbl">Logs</div>
  <div className="hz-score-bar">
    <div className="hz-score-fill" style={{ width: '77%', background: 'var(--hz-info)' }} />
  </div>
</div>
// Grade color: A→ok / B→info / C→warn / D→crit
// Animate bar width from 0 to score% on mount: 0.6s cubic-bezier(0.4,0,0.2,1)
```

### Finding Card

```tsx
<div className="hz-fc">
  <div className="hz-fc-bar hz-fc-bar-crit" />
  <div>
    <div className="hz-fc-title">Missing span on error path</div>
